rule-4-14-a.test_description: A building has one building segment and one zone. The space in the zone has its lighting space type defined as a computer room and the proposed room equipment power density exceeds 20 W/ft2.

standard.rule_description: A computer room is defined as a room whose primary function is to house equipment for the processing and storage of electronic data and that has a design electronic data equipment power density exceeding 20 W/ft2 of conditioned floor area.

rule-4-14-b.test_description: A building has one building segment and one zone. The space in the zone has its lighting space type defined as a computer room and the proposed room equipment power density does not exceed 20 W/ft2.
rule-4-14-b.expected_raised_message_includes: The space has been classed as a computer room in terms of the lighting space type but the electronic data equipment power density does not appear to exceed 20 w/sf.

standard.rule_description: A computer room is defined as a room whose primary function is to house equipment for the processing and storage of electronic data and that has a design electronic data equipment power density exceeding 20 W/ft2 of conditioned floor area.
